======================================================
04 - FINAL ANALYTICAL SUMMARY
======================================================


Description:
This section contains the final analytical outputs of the
project, combining the results of previous SQL analysis
into structured and ready-to-use datasets.

While earlier sections (01, 02, and 03) focused on
exploration and detailed analysis, this section
consolidates the most important insights into compact
summary tables.

The goal is to provide:
- a clear overview of the dataset
- a complete evaluation of team performance
- and a detailed analysis of team matchups


------------------------------------------------------
Structure of the Section
------------------------------------------------------

The section is divided into three main parts:

04_01 – General Summary  
Provides a high-level overview of the dataset, including
size, scoring behavior, match outcomes, and discipline.

04_02 – Team Summary  
Presents a complete performance profile for each team,
including participation, results, efficiency, and
scoring metrics.

04_03 – Matchup Summary  (matches>10)
Analyzes head-to-head matchups between teams, including
results, scoring patterns, and match intensity.


------------------------------------------------------
Purpose of the Outputs
------------------------------------------------------

All outputs in this section are designed to be:

- compact and easy to interpret
- suitable for CSV export
- ready for visualization and further analysis in Python

These datasets (04_01, 04_02, and 04_03) are specifically
structured to support data analytics and forecasting
tasks using Python, enabling further exploration through
statistical analysis, visualization, and predictive
modeling.

Together, they form a complete analytical view of the
dataset at three levels:
- global (dataset)
- individual (team)
- relational (matchup)